{[%evp 0,107,18,12,12,12,12,12,12,8,6,3,24,5,15,-14,5,19,26,20,20,20,15,15,11,11,11,19,27,0,4,0,40,26,19,19,17,11,19,19,28,8,30,9,9,0,0,-7,-7,-15,26,37,128,128,135,135,119,121,109,102,111,92,128,128,133,130,123,122,125,125,125,125,117,131,125,139,121,142,138,152,171,210,209,216,221,201,134,90,323,315,354,355,395,393,395,487,627,395,530,513,530,556,556,608,821,1113,1314,1289,1289,1289]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. Nc3 a6 6. a4 d6 7. h3 h6 8. Be3 O-O 9. O-O Bxe3 10. fxe3 Be6 11. Nd2 Bxc4 12. Nxc4 d5 13. exd5 Nxd5 14. e4 Nf4 (14... Nxc3 15. bxc3 {Understanding that in such a position he will be left with the wrong knight, Black tries to mantain the other one in the game. But it will not solve all of his problems!}) 15. Kh2 Ng6 16. a5 {Fixing the queenside} Qd7 17. Nd5 Nce7 18. Nde3 {Having more space, White avoids exchanges!} f6 19. g3 $1 {An important move. restricting the g6-knight.} Rad8 20. h4 Nh8 21. Rf2 Nf7 22. Qh5 Nd6 23. Raf1 Nxc4 24. Nxc4 Qe8 25. Qg4 Nc6 {Black falls under pressure.} ({Another option would have been} 25... Qc6 {Of course, we take white. But Black is in the game here.}) 26. Rxf6 $18 Rxf6 27. Rxf6 h5 28. Qg5 Qe7 29. Rf5 Qxg5 30. hxg5 Rf8 31. Kh3 g6 32. Rxf8+ Kxf8 33. c3 Ke7 34. g4 hxg4+ 35. Kxg4 Ke6 36. Kf3 Nd8 37. d4 Nf7 38. Kg4 exd4 39. cxd4 Ke7 40. Kf4 Nd8 41. d5 c6 42. b4 cxd5 43. exd5 Kd7 44. Ne5+ Kd6 45. Ke4 Kc7 46. Nxg6 Nf7 47. Kf5 Nd6+ 48. Kf4 Nc4 49. Ne5 Nd6 50. g6 Ne8 51. Nf7 Kd7 52. Ke5 Ke7 53. Nh6 Kd7 54. Nf5 1-0

