{[%evp 0,73,34,30,23,25,4,18,23,15,15,2,22,17,28,16,18,23,23,24,19,15,23,26,20,16,12,24,23,0,21,20,31,46,53,26,12,-9,22,5,45,8,42,25,48,65,57,46,60,49,102,122,92,73,98,49,62,39,34,27,27,-17,297,269,464,418,379,379,412,402,422,433,527,525,550,503]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. d3 h6 6. h3 a6 7. a4 d6 8. Be3 Bxe3 9. fxe3 Be6 10. Nd2 Bxc4 11. Nxc4 O-O 12. O-O d5 13. exd5 Nxd5 14. e4 Nxc3 15. bxc3 b5 16. Ne3 Ne7 17. Rf3 ({Another option would have been} 17. Qh5 {preparing the rook lift Rf3-g3. In my opinion, this is even more precise.} Qd6 {is not possible, because of} 18. axb5 axb5 19. Rxa8 Rxa8 20. Rxf7 {White is winning.}) 17... Qd7 18. Rg3 Qe6 19. Qh5 {The difference between 17.Qh5 directly and 17.Rf3 is exactly that Black can move his queen to e6 more quickly.} Kh7 20. Kh2 g6 21. Qg4 Qc6 22. axb5 axb5 23. Rf1 Ra6 24. Qh4 $18 {Everyone is attacking! White is just crushing.} Qe8 25. Rgf3 Rc6 26. d4 Ng8 27. Nd5 exd4 28. cxd4 Rxc2 29. e5 c5 30. Nf4 f6 31. Nxg6 Kxg6 32. Qe4+ Kg7 33. Qxc2 cxd4 34. Qc7+ Qf7 35. exf6+ Nxf6 36. Qe5 d3 37. Rxd3 1-0

