{[#]} {How should White continue?} 6. Bg5 {This move itself is not new. But after} h6 {White will play} 7. Bh4 $5 {The point! This move is considered to be bad in all the sources that I found about this position. However, after analyzing it more deeply, I found that this is completely wrong, and the move is totally playable. This is a very interesting thing because not only are the positions arising from it interesting, but we are also going to surprise our opponents when we play it. I will explain all the details of this position in our theoretical coverage. If the positions are too sharp for your taste, don't worry! Be3 is also a totally playable move, and you can vary between the two without any problems. But for this survey, I will focus our analysis on the Bg5-Bh4 idea.} (7. Bxf6 {is what theory suggests, but I dislike the resulting positions. Black is just ok here.}) *

