{[#]} {How should White continue?} 6. h3 {And here, Black has nowhere to go; he will be forced to commit to something (d6, a6, or h6). And after all these moves, we can just transpose to the lines that we analyzed if we want. So this 0-0 move has no independent value. And as I explain in the theoretical part, it even has some drawbacks in certain lines. But we will talk about them soon.} (6. Bg5 $5 {Can also by tried. Nevertheless, I am not a big fan of this move because Black has not committed to ...a7-a6.}) 6... h6 (6... d6 7. Na4) (6... a6 7. Bg5) 7. O-O a6 8. Be3 *

